---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Our Story"
  description="Nat and Marc from Brisbane, QLD made one foldable beach chair. Three years, many revisions, and no shortcuts. This is the Hammo story."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero" aria-labelledby="about-hero-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-hero-grid">
        <div class="about-hero-text">
          <span
            class="text-label"
            style="color: var(--accent); display: block; margin-bottom: 16px;"
            >The Founders</span
          >
          <h1
            class="display-xl"
            id="about-hero-heading"
            style="margin-bottom: 24px;"
          >
            Nat and Marc.<br /><em>From Brisbane.</em>
          </h1>
          <p
            class="text-body"
            style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 46ch;"
          >
            Hammo started as a holiday frustration and became a three-year
            project. The idea was simple: make one beach chair properly. What
            that actually meant took a lot longer to figure out.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-hero-visual">
          <div class="media-frame">
            <svg
              viewBox="0 0 600 350"
              aria-label="Graphic of Queensland coastline — the inspiration for Hammo"
              role="img"
            >
              <defs>
                <linearGradient
                  id="sand-grad"
                  x1="0%"
                  y1="0%"
                  x2="0%"
                  y2="100%"
                >
                  <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--paper-soft)"></stop>
                  <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--paper-dark)"></stop>
                </linearGradient>
              </defs>
              <rect width="600" height="350" fill="var(--paper-soft)"></rect>
              <path
                d="M 0 200 C 150 180, 200 240, 400 210 C 500 190, 550 220, 600 200 L 600 350 L 0 350 Z"
                fill="url(#sand-grad)"></path>
              <path
                d="M 0 240 Q 180 200, 360 260 T 600 220"
                fill="none"
                stroke="var(--ink-mute)"
                stroke-width="1.25"
                opacity="0.3"></path>
              <path
                d="M 0 265 Q 220 230, 440 280 T 600 245"
                fill="none"
                stroke="var(--border)"
                stroke-width="1"></path>
              <circle
                cx="300"
                cy="130"
                r="50"
                fill="var(--accent)"
                opacity="0.06"></circle>
              <path
                d="M 450 210 L 510 140 L 540 145 L 600 90 L 600 350 L 450 350 Z"
                fill="var(--paper-dark)"
                opacity="0.75"></path>
              <path
                d="M 450 210 L 510 140 L 540 145 L 600 90"
                stroke="var(--ink)"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                fill="none"></path>
              <text
                x="32"
                y="318"
                font-family="var(--font-body)"
                font-size="11"
                fill="var(--ink-mute)"
                >BRISBANE, QLD — 27.4698° S, 153.0251° E</text
              >
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder story pullquote -->
  <section class="brand-mission-quote" aria-label="Founder quote">
    <div class="container">
      <blockquote style="margin: 0; padding: 0; text-align: left;">
        <p
          class="display-lm"
          style="line-height: 1.45; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 24px; color: var(--paper);"
        >
          "We were on holiday with the kids. We had a beach chair that took up
          the entire boot, weighed more than our toddler, and still managed to
          be uncomfortable. We thought: this is the one thing that should be
          easy."
        </p>
        <cite
          class="text-label"
          style="font-style: normal; color: var(--ink-mute); display: block;"
          >— Nat, Co-Founder</cite
        >
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Design story chapters -->
  <section class="timeline-section" aria-labelledby="timeline-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 64px;">
        <span
          class="text-label"
          style="color: var(--ink-soft); display: block; margin-bottom: 12px;"
          >Three Years in the Making</span
        >
        <h2 class="display-l" id="timeline-heading">
          From a holiday idea<br /><em>to a proper chair.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-body" style="color: var(--ink-soft); margin-top: 16px;">
          Nat and Marc spent three years designing, testing, and revising the
          Hammo chair. No shortcuts. No compromises on comfort or build quality.
          Every revision was made with one question in mind: is this actually
          easier to live with?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-flow">
        <!-- Chapter 1 -->
        <article class="timeline-node">
          <div class="timeline-number-col">
            <span class="node-number">01</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content-col">
            <h3 class="display-m" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
              The holiday that started it
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-body"
              style="color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 24px;"
            >
              Nat and Marc were on a family holiday when the idea first landed.
              Not as a business plan — just as a complaint. Every beach chair
              they'd ever owned was either too heavy, too big, too ugly, or too
              flimsy. Usually all four. They started sketching on a napkin.
            </p>
            <div class="node-drawing">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 450 180"
                aria-label="Napkin sketch of the original Hammo chair concept"
                role="img"
              >
                <rect width="450" height="180" fill="var(--paper-soft)"></rect>
                <path
                  d="M 50 140 Q 150 100, 220 120 T 380 90"
                  stroke="var(--ink-mute)"
                  stroke-width="1.25"
                  stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                  fill="none"></path>
                <path
                  d="M 120 150 L 260 40"
                  stroke="var(--ink-soft)"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                <path
                  d="M 280 150 L 100 80"
                  stroke="var(--ink-soft)"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                <text
                  x="20"
                  y="32"
                  font-family="var(--font-mono)"
                  font-size="10"
                  fill="var(--accent)">SKETCH V0.1 — HOLIDAY NAPKIN</text
                >
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Chapter 2 -->
        <article class="timeline-node">
          <div class="timeline-number-col">
            <span class="node-number">02</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content-col">
            <h3 class="display-m" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
              Three years of revisions
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-body"
              style="color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 24px;"
            >
              The chair went through many versions. The frame changed. The
              canvas sling changed. The way it folded changed. Each revision was
              tested in the real world — at the beach, in the car, in the
              hallway, on planes. If it didn't pass the actual use test, it went
              back to the drawing board.
            </p>
            <div class="node-drawing">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 450 180"
                aria-label="Revision comparison diagram"
                role="img"
              >
                <rect width="450" height="180" fill="var(--paper-soft)"></rect>
                <circle
                  cx="225"
                  cy="90"
                  r="50"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="var(--accent)"
                  stroke-width="1.5"></circle>
                <path
                  d="M 175 90 L 275 90 M 225 40 L 225 140"
                  stroke="var(--border)"
                  stroke-width="1"></path>
                <text
                  x="20"
                  y="32"
                  font-family="var(--font-mono)"
                  font-size="10"
                  fill="var(--ink-soft)">REVISION CYCLE — MANY ITERATIONS</text
                >
                <text
                  x="225"
                  y="105"
                  font-family="var(--font-mono)"
                  font-size="11"
                  text-anchor="middle"
                  fill="var(--ink)">NO SHORTCUTS</text
                >
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Chapter 3 -->
        <article class="timeline-node">
          <div class="timeline-number-col">
            <span class="node-number">03</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content-col">
            <h3 class="display-m" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
              One product, shipped personally
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-body"
              style="color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 24px;"
            >
              When Hammo launched, Nat and Marc packed and shipped every single
              order themselves. They still do. It's not the most scalable model,
              but it means every chair that leaves their hands has been touched
              by the people who designed it. That feels important to them.
            </p>
            <div class="node-drawing">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 450 180"
                aria-label="Chair folded flat profile"
                role="img"
              >
                <rect width="450" height="180" fill="var(--paper-soft)"></rect>
                <rect
                  x="50"
                  y="80"
                  width="350"
                  height="12"
                  rx="4"
                  fill="var(--paper-dark)"
                  stroke="var(--ink)"
                  stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <circle cx="90" cy="86" r="4" fill="var(--accent)"></circle>
                <circle cx="360" cy="86" r="4" fill="var(--accent)"></circle>
                <path
                  d="M 410 76 L 415 76 L 415 96 L 410 96"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="var(--ink)"
                  stroke-width="1"></path>
                <text
                  x="425"
                  y="90"
                  font-family="var(--font-mono)"
                  font-size="11"
                  fill="var(--ink)">flat</text
                >
                <text
                  x="20"
                  y="32"
                  font-family="var(--font-mono)"
                  font-size="10"
                  fill="var(--ink-soft)"
                  >FINAL FORM — FOLDS LIKE A YOGA MAT</text
                >
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero section */
  .about-hero {
    padding-block: 80px 60px;
    background-color: var(--paper);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media (min-width: 992px) {
    .about-hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.1fr;
      gap: 64px;
    }
  }

  .about-hero-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .about-hero-visual {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .media-frame {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background-color: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: 12px;
  }

  .media-frame svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Quote section — dark */
  .brand-mission-quote {
    padding-block: 80px;
    background-color: var(--ink);
    border-block: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline-section {
    padding-block: 80px;
    background-color: var(--paper);
  }

  .timeline-flow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 64px;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin-left: 12px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .timeline-flow {
      padding-left: 48px;
      margin-left: 24px;
    }
  }

  .timeline-node {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline-node::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;
    left: -32.5px;
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    border: 3px solid var(--paper);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--ink);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .timeline-node::before {
      left: -56.5px;
    }
  }

  .node-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 54px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 0.9;
  }

  .timeline-content-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .node-drawing {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 500px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background-color: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: 8px;
  }

  .node-drawing svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }
</style>
